ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_0: Did He not bring all their schemes to nothing,
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_1: Did He not make their plan go wrong,
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_2: Did He not bring their plan to naught?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_3: Did He not cause their evil plots to fail
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_4: Did He not put their scheme into ruin?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_5: Did He not make their plot go astray
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_6: Did He not cause their war to end in confusion,
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_7: Did He not make their guile to go astray?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_8: Did He not bring their stratagem to naught,
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_9: Did He not foil their strategy
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_10: Put He not their stratagem to straying.
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_11: Did He not make their stratagems go awry,
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_12: Did He not make their treacherous plan go astray?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_13: Did He not make their plot go astray?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_14: Did He not cause their schemes to go astray?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_15: Did He not make their plan go wrong?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_16: Did He not make their plan into misguidance?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_17: [105:2] Did He not make — that is to say, He did [indeed] make — their stratagem, to destroy the Ka‘ba, go astray, [ending up] in failure and destruction,
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_18: (Did He not bring their stratagem) their scheming (to naught) to utter loss,
